TITLE: Creating HTML Table from Matrix using D3.js Data Join
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create an HTML table by binding a 2D array of numbers using nested data joins with D3.js selection methods.
SOURCE: https://github.com/d3/d3/blob/main/docs/d3-selection/joining.md#2025-04-11_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const matrix = [
  [11975,  5871, 8916, 2868],
  [ 1951, 10048, 2060, 6171],
  [ 8010, 16145, 8090, 8045],
  [ 1013,   990,  940, 6907]
];

d3.select("body")
  .append("table")
  .selectAll("tr")
  .data(matrix)
  .join("tr")
  .selectAll("td")
  .data(d => d)
  .join("td")
    .text(d => d);
```

