TITLE: Preparing Data for D3 Treemap Layout in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows the process of preparing hierarchical data for a treemap layout, including summing values and sorting nodes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/d3/d3/blob/main/docs/d3-hierarchy/hierarchy.md#2025-04-11_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// Construct the treemap layout.
const treemap = d3.treemap();
treemap.size([width, height]);
treemap.padding(2);

// Sum and sort the data.
root.sum((d) => d.value);
root.sort((a, b) => b.height - a.height || b.value - a.value);

// Compute the treemap layout.
treemap(root);

// Retrieve all descendant nodes.
const nodes = root.descendants();
```

