TITLE: Implementing a Custom Force in D3 Force Simulation in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Creates a custom force function that moves nodes toward the origin. The function applies a force proportional to each node's distance from the origin, scaled by the alpha parameter and a constant factor.
SOURCE: https://github.com/d3/d3/blob/main/docs/d3-force/simulation.md#2025-04-11_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function force(alpha) {
  for (let i = 0, n = nodes.length, node, k = alpha * 0.1; i < n; ++i) {
    node = nodes[i];
    node.vx -= node.x * k;
    node.vy -= node.y * k;
  }
}
```

