TITLE: Custom Subject Accessor for Canvas-Based Circle Dragging
DESCRIPTION: A custom subject accessor function that finds the closest circle to the pointer within a given radius. This is useful for canvas-based visualizations where exact element detection is needed.
SOURCE: https://github.com/d3/d3/blob/main/docs/d3-drag.md#2025-04-11_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function subject(event) {
  let n = circles.length,
      i,
      dx,
      dy,
      d2,
      s2 = radius * radius,
      circle,
      subject;

  for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
    circle = circles[i];
    dx = event.x - circle.x;
    dy = event.y - circle.y;
    d2 = dx * dx + dy * dy;
    if (d2 < s2) subject = circle, s2 = d2;
  }

  return subject;
}
```

