TITLE: Implementing Temporary Drag Event Listeners in D3.js
DESCRIPTION: Example of using event.on to register temporary drag and end event listeners within a start event handler. This pattern creates closure functions that manage the visual state of a dragged circle element during a drag operation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/d3/d3/blob/main/docs/d3-drag.md#2025-04-11_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function started(event) {
  const circle = d3.select(this).classed("dragging", true);
  const dragged = (event, d) => circle.raise().attr("cx", d.x = event.x).attr("cy", d.y = event.y);
  const ended = () => circle.classed("dragging", false);
  event.on("drag", dragged).on("end", ended);
}
```

