TITLE: Using d3.greatestIndex with comparators in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Returns the index of the greatest element according to a specified comparator or accessor. Returns -1 if the iterable contains no comparable elements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/d3/d3/blob/main/docs/d3-array/summarize.md#2025-04-11_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const array = [{foo: 42}, {foo: 91}];
d3.greatestIndex(array, (a, b) => a.foo - b.foo); // 1
d3.greatestIndex(array, (a, b) => b.foo - a.foo); // 0
d3.greatestIndex(array, (d) => d.foo); // 1
```

