TITLE: Implementing rescaleX for Transforming Scale Domains in D3
DESCRIPTION: This function returns a copy of a continuous scale with a transformed domain. It works by applying inverse x-transform on the scale's range and then computing the corresponding domain using the inverse scale. The original scale is not modified.
SOURCE: https://github.com/d3/d3/blob/main/docs/d3-zoom.md#2025-04-11_snippet_18

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function rescaleX(x) {
  var range = x.range().map(transform.invertX, transform),
      domain = range.map(x.invert, x);
  return x.copy().domain(domain);
}
```

